Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine pink-buff. Circular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie diary Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 121, 6 or 200, 2 From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0314.35.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0421)
